## Summary: Your Internal Load Monitoring Checklist

Use this as your starting point this week:

- [ ] Choose a consistent RPE scale (CR10 or 1–10 simplified)
- [ ] Set up post-session RPE collection — ideally within 30 minutes of finishing
- [ ] Add 3–4 wellness questions: sleep, soreness, fatigue, mood
- [ ] Record session duration for every training session and match
- [ ] Calculate weekly ACWR for each player
- [ ] Review ACWR and wellness trends before planning your next block
- [ ] Flag any athlete with ACWR above 1.3 for a load reduction review
- [ ] Monitor compliance — aim for 80%+ submission rates
- [ ] Share insights with your coaching and medical staff regularly
- [ ] Reassess your approach monthly and adjust based on what the data shows

> You don't need expensive technology to protect your athletes. You need consistent data, clear thresholds, and the discipline to act on what you see. That's within reach for every club — regardless of budget.